
How to build and use js2mpl

  1. cd to your work area and get source code from the following git repositories
     note all the steps assume you are in the work directory
      % git clone http://name:passwd@12.234.36.18/Mempool.git
      % git clone http://name:passwd@12.234.36.18/mapleir.git
      % git clone http://name:passwd@12.234.36.18/maplebe.git
      % git clone http://name:passwd@12.234.36.18/libjsrt.git
      % git clone http://name:passwd@12.234.36.18/mozjs.git
      % git clone http://name:passwd@12.234.36.18/js2mpl.git

     at this point, the directory structure should look like
       maple
         |- js2mpl
              |- include
              |- Makefile
              |- Makefile.in
              |- README
              |- src
              |- tests
         |- libjsrt
         |- maplebe
         |- mapleir
         |- Mempool
         |- mozjs
              |- Makefile
              |- mozjs-31.2.0
              |- README

  2. build Mempool, mapleir, maplebe, libjsrt
      % cd Mempool/src; make
      % cd mapleir; make
      % cd maplebe; make
      % cd libjsrt; make

  3. build mozjs
      % cd mozjs; make config; make

  4. build js2mpl
      % cd js2mpl; make

  5. run regression
      % cd js2mpl/tests; make regression
